Sentencas: In the present work, a metal supported SOFC half-cell was fabricated by means of plasma spray.
Titulo: Manufacturing of high performance solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with atmospheric plasma spraying (APS) and plasma spray-physical vapor deposition (PS-PVD)

Sentencas: As support, a Fe-Cr alloy with a porous structure was used.
Titulo: Manufacturing of high performance solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with atmospheric plasma spraying (APS) and plasma spray-physical vapor deposition (PS-PVD)

Sentencas: The anode and electrolyte were applied using atmospheric plasma spray (APS) and plasma spray-physical vapor deposition (PS-PVD), respectively.
Titulo: Manufacturing of high performance solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with atmospheric plasma spraying (APS) and plasma spray-physical vapor deposition (PS-PVD)

Sentencas: A standard Ni/YSZ (coat mix) powder was used for the anode and the cathode layer consisted of a screen-printed La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 - delta (LSCF) non-sintered paste.
Titulo: Manufacturing of high performance solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with atmospheric plasma spraying (APS) and plasma spray-physical vapor deposition (PS-PVD)

Sentencas: The development of a thin, dense, gas-tight8 YSZ electrolyte was the key issue of this work Analysis of microstructure, phases, and gas-tightness were carried out for various processing conditions.
Titulo: Manufacturing of high performance solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with atmospheric plasma spraying (APS) and plasma spray-physical vapor deposition (PS-PVD)

Sentencas: Different parameters were varied, such as: powder feed rate and carrier gas flow rate, robot speed, spraying distance and plasma gas composition.
Titulo: Manufacturing of high performance solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with atmospheric plasma spraying (APS) and plasma spray-physical vapor deposition (PS-PVD)

Sentencas: A partially reduced anode coating with 9% porosity and a gas-tight 26 Inn electrolyte layer were obtained.
Titulo: Manufacturing of high performance solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with atmospheric plasma spraying (APS) and plasma spray-physical vapor deposition (PS-PVD)

Sentencas: Such an assembly was air-tight and delivered a cell with an acceptable open circuit voltage (OCV) and an excellent performance of 1 A/cm(2) at 800 degrees C and 0.7 V. (C) 2016 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.
Titulo: Manufacturing of high performance solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with atmospheric plasma spraying (APS) and plasma spray-physical vapor deposition (PS-PVD)
